# ─── Firebase config (developer-supplied) ─────────────────────────────────────
# Client-side Firebase config, kept OUT of the repo as a matter of hygiene.
# These are NOT high-severity secrets (Firestore security rules are the real
# protection), but each developer/CI supplies their own locally. To build after
# cloning, run `flutterfire configure` (regenerates firebase_options.dart +
# platform files) or drop in your project's copies.
android/app/google-services.json
lib/firebase_options.dart
ios/Runner/GoogleService-Info.plist
macos/Runner/GoogleService-Info.plist
graphify-out/

# ─── Claude Code local settings ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# Per-developer tool-permission grants that accumulate as you work. Purely local
# machine state, so it must not ride along in feature commits. `settings.json`
# (shared project config) is deliberately NOT ignored.
.claude/settings.local.json
